    "created_at": "2024-08-15T06:09:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-08-15T06:09:04Z",
    "body": "Because the prompt is set via the `precmd` function, this normally requires SOME sort of interaction occur, as when it first loads, no command has yet been executed.\r\nHowever, the easiest resolution is to execute that `precmd` on initialization.\r\n\r\nI sorted this by adding the `starship_precmd` directly after initializing starship.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\neval $(starship init bash)\r\n# Execute the precmd to set initial PS1\r\nstarship_precmd\r\n```",
